             <h1 class="single">ABOUT  Immaculate Heart of Mary College-Parañaque</h1>
                        <br/>
                        <center>
                                <img src="Content/images/portfolio/1.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt=""  height="600" width="1000"/>
                       
                        <br/><br />
                        <p class="solid">
                            Immaculate Heart of Mary College-Parañaque (IHMC-P, formerly known as Immaculate Heart of Mary School-Parañaque; colloquially, "Imma") is a Private, Roman Catholic, educational institution run by the Franciscan Sisters of the Sacred Hearts. It is located on a 2.5 Hectare Lot on both sides of St. Dominic Savio Street in Better Living Subdivision, Parañaque City. The college was established in 1979 offering elementary education, then in 1983 it opened its doors to its first batch of high school students. The College Department was established in 2002. Admission is open to students of different religion and nationality.
                        </p>

                        <br/><br />                    
                        <h5  class="solid"><strong>H I S T O R Y</strong></h5><br />
                        <p class="solid">
                            The Manila Cathedral School was founded in 1949 where it catered education for
                            primary up to tertiary level. The Manila Cathedral School envision as an Archdiocesan center
                            of Catholic education and formation among the poor youth of Tondo, committed to the
                            Church’s continuing mission of Evangelization. The School has been directed by Catholic
                            Priest up to present day. At present, the school is offering nursery up to senior high school
                            education supported by advance educational materials to provide quality education.
                        </p>

                        <br/><br />
                        <h5  class="solid"><strong>M I S S I O N</strong></h5><br />
                        <p class="solid">
                           Guided by the Franciscan motto, “My God and My All”, we promote an education which recognizes the omnipotence of God and the nothingness of man
                           As a learning community, IHMC - Parañaque provides a dynamic, inclusive and integrated Immaculatinian education where a collegial group of administrators, faculty, staff, parents and students themselves are united in their commitment to student learning.
                           As a Filipino learning community, IHMC-Parañaque recognizes the partnership of parents and teachers as facilitators of learning for a deeper appreciation of their own cultural heritage.
                           As a Catholic learning community, IHMC-Parañaque fosters a nurturing and caring atmosphere where students develop a strong spiritual and academic foundation based on Gospel values for effective transformational Catholic leaders.
                           As a Franciscan learning community, IHMC-Parañaque views humanity as a family; values the integrity of creation and care for mother earth; works for peace and social justice and generously volunteers services.
                        </p>

                        <br/><br />
                        <h5 class="solid"><strong>V  I  S  I  O  N</strong></h5><br />
                        <p class="solid">Immaculate Heart of Mary College - Parañaque is committed to produce totally integrated persons of Catholic faith, reason and charity for transformational leadership in the global society.</p>
